Incident Away Teamwill be carried out by the Labuan Office and other functions will be carried out by the Corporate Office.7.2.5COMMUNICATION WITH OWNERS AND OTHERSIn case of any casualty the Owners’ Person In Charge (PIC) should be notified of the event within 30 minutes of the company(Superintendent or any other responsible person receiving the first notification) being made aware.7.3ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITIES1. MANAGING DIRECTOR (MD)Back up: General Manager1) To ensure that adequate resources to deal with the contingency are available which include:a) Provision of funds.b) To provide additional man power.c) To provide for additional equipment such as mobile phone etc.2) To monitor the actions of the Company Response Team and the field command post and provide necessary guidance/ support.3) To liaise with the owners.4) He shall issue media statements and deal with the media as required.5) He shall be the sole spokesman with the media and be assisted by the Communication team.6) He shall conduct brief meetings at frequent intervals so that all members of the ERT can appraise other members ERT on tasksaccomplished.7) To review the post incident analysis.2. INCIDENT COMMANDERPIC: Designated Person Ashore (DPA)Alternate: Alternate Designated Person Ashore (DPA)1) Upon receipt of the initial notification, to act as ‘Incident Commander’.2) To act as overall in-charge of management of incident. Leads, commands, controls and manages the incident.3) Determines incident potential and initiates ‘Company Response Team’.4) Ensures incident objectives are developed and pursued.5) To immediately reply to the initial notification message from the vessel. This must include following standard instructions to thevessel:a) All documents to be preserved intactb) No falsification of documentsc) Save VDR/ SVDR datad) Emergency Alcohol Test6)To carry out the initial notification as laid down in Section 7.2.17) To liaise with the other members of the Emergency Response Team to take the necessary action to deal with the contingency aslaid down in Section 7.5.8) Responsible to ensure accurate Situation Report (SITREP) is sent out at regular interval.9) To keep the Managing Director advised of the developments.10) To carry out post incident analysis.11) To take corrective measures as required by the conclusion of post incident analysis.12) Liaises with P&I Club, H&M Underwriters, National Authority, Legal Consultant etc as required.13) Inform Flag state.14) Security Related Issues - Liaise with PFSO and Port Authority.15) Maintains incident summary log.3. EMERGENCY RESPONSE ADVISEPIC: General ManagerAlternate: General Manager Tech & Operations1) Provides advice to Incident Commander, Communication Team, Operations/ Planning Chief and Field Command Post.2) Monitors and supports all key processes throughout the emergency response.3) To mobilize the necessary resources to deal with the contingency.4) To seek expert help from makers/ relevant authorities if required.
